baseline.comment:
Baseline for first component - Development of inter-municipal cooperation (IMC)

Weak coordination among municipalities;
Insufficient sources to fund IMC (especially among small municipalities);
More information and guideline needed to form sustainable IMC arrangements;
Need for applying experiences of other countries in the area of IMC to Montenegro;

Baseline for second component - development of Municipal Assemblies in Montenegro

Lack of available data at the local level, whether on the functioning of local governance institutions or on specific municipal needs;
Existence of inactive permanent or temporary bodies in a Municipal Assembly;
Lack of an electronic database or systematic overview of decisions taken by a Municipal Assembly and to what extent they have been implemented;
Weak oversight by a Municipal Assembly over a municipal administration;
Inactive citizen participation into public hearings or sessions held at a Municipal Assembly;
Municipal Assemblys weak oversight role over a mayor and an administration;
Poor participation of women and gender blind policies;

Baseline for third component - Support the implementation of cap.dev.prog. in line with NTS - IPA 2010:
-Need for an improvement of institutional/organizational set up for proper implementation of quality training programmes;

